# {{ project_name | pascal }} - Azure Event Hubs Consumer

Auto-generated Go consumer for Azure Event Hubs with broker-free test seams and CloudEvents dispatch.

## Quick start

Implement `{{ class_name }}Handler`, then create the consumer:

```go
consumer, err := {{ project_name | snake }}.New{{ class_name }}(
    "Endpoint=sb://...;SharedAccessKeyName=...;SharedAccessKey=...",
    "event-hub-name",
    "0",
    handler,
)
if err != nil {
    panic(err)
}
defer consumer.Close(context.Background())

if err := consumer.Start(context.Background()); err != nil {
    panic(err)
}
```

Use `New{{ class_name }}WithReceiver` to unit-test with a fake receiver. Binary CloudEvents are read from Event Hubs application properties using the `cloudEvents:` prefix; structured CloudEvents are decoded from `application/cloudevents+json` bodies.

## Dependencies

- `github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-go/sdk/messaging/azeventhubs`
- `github.com/cloudevents/sdk-go/v2`
